# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# IVAE Studios — Cloudflare Pages response headers
# ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Cloudflare reads this file at the repo root (netlify.toml is ignored
# — see CLAUDE.md). Order matters: more-specific rules MUST appear
# before broader catch-alls because Pages MERGES Cache-Control values
# across matching rules. Don't introduce a wider /*.js or /*.css
# catch-all above the gallery rules.
#
# Comment syntax: '#' is only honored at the start of a line, NOT
# indented inside a rule block — the parser treats indented lines as
# header values. All annotation comments live at column 0 between
# rule blocks.
#
# This file is split into three layers:
#   1. /*  → site-wide security headers (CSP, HSTS, Permissions-Policy…)
#   2. Per-asset Cache-Control rules (fonts, images, CSS/JS, HTML)
#   3. Gallery sub-app overrides (out-of-scope for the redesign — these
#      sections are preserved verbatim from before the refactor).
# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════


# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# 1 · GLOBAL SECURITY HEADERS (apply to every response)
# ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# Strict-Transport-Security: 2-year HSTS with includeSubDomains and
# preload. Opts the apex into the browser HSTS preload list (one-way
# commitment — only safe to enable once every subdomain is HTTPS-only,
# which is true here: Cloudflare Pages + the gallery subdomain both
# serve HTTPS exclusively).
#
# X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff stops the browser from MIME-sniffing
# a response body. If we serve a .json with the wrong Content-Type,
# the browser must NOT execute it as JS.
#
# X-Frame-Options: DENY — disallow ANY framing of the site. Pairs with
# `frame-ancestors 'none'` in CSP (X-Frame-Options is the legacy
# fallback for old browsers).
#
# Referrer-Policy: strict-origin-when-cross-origin — when linking
# off-site, send only the origin (https://ivaestudios.com) — never
# the path or query. Within the same origin we still send the full
# referrer so analytics can attribute internal flows.
#
# Permissions-Policy: aggressive deny-list of every API the site does
# not use. An attacker who lands an XSS still cannot pop the camera,
# mic, GPS, payment sheet, USB device, etc. Any feature added later
# must be explicitly opted-in.
#
# Cross-Origin-Opener-Policy: same-origin — page is its own browsing
# context group, no window.opener leaks from popups we open.
# Cross-Origin-Resource-Policy: same-site — ivaestudios.com subdomains
# (assets.*, gallery.*) can load our resources, unrelated origins
# cannot hot-link them as rendered subresources.
#
# Content-Security-Policy — built from an audit of every <link>, <img>,
# <script>, <iframe> and fetch() call across the site:
#
#   • default-src 'self'                   fall-through deny-by-default.
#   • script-src 'self'                    redesign-era JS lives in /js/.
#                'unsafe-inline'           TECH DEBT: legacy pages still
#                                          ship inline <script> blocks
#                                          (admin.html login, the
#                                          focal-admin auth shim on
#                                          post-bachelorette-* and
#                                          es/manejo-redes-sociales,
#                                          and the old cenote /
#                                          trash-the-dress posts).
#                                          REMOVE this token once
#                                          Oleada 4 (blog refactor) +
#                                          Oleada 6 (legacy svc pages)
#                                          migrate them to external
#                                          scripts.
#                https://static.cloudflareinsights.com
#                                          Cloudflare Web Analytics
#                                          beacon — privacy.html
#                                          confirms we use this in lieu
#                                          of Google Analytics.
#   • style-src  'self'                    main.css, blog.css, print.css.
#                'unsafe-inline'           REQUIRED: index.html and the
#                                          other top-level pages embed
#                                          a small <style> block for
#                                          the .skip-link a11y helper.
#                https://fonts.googleapis.com
#                                          legacy: 4 unmigrated pages
#                                          still pull Cormorant/Syne
#                                          from Google Fonts. Remove
#                                          once Oleada 4 swaps them
#                                          to self-hosted.
#   • img-src    'self' data:              local /images/ + tiny inline
#                                          PNGs/SVGs.
#                https://assets.ivaestudios.com
#                                          image CDN (blog OG images,
#                                          wordmark, vianey-diaz.jpg).
#   • font-src   'self' data:              self-hosted brand WOFF2.
#                https://fonts.gstatic.com legacy companion to the
#                                          Google Fonts <link> above.
#   • connect-src 'self'                   newsletter + contact forms
#                                          POST to /api/* (same origin).
#                 https://cloudflareinsights.com
#                                          beacon endpoint for the
#                                          Web Analytics RUM call.
#   • frame-ancestors 'none'               nobody may iframe us.
#   • frame-src 'none'                     we don't embed third-party
#                                          iframes (no YouTube, no
#                                          Maps embed, no Instagram).
#   • base-uri 'self'                      block <base href> hijacking.
#   • form-action 'self'                   forms can only POST to our
#                                          own /api/* endpoints.
#   • object-src 'none'                    no <object>/<embed>/<applet>.
#   • upgrade-insecure-requests            auto-rewrite stray http://
#                                          subresources to https://.
#
# NOTE: ld+json schema blocks use type="application/ld+json" (data,
# not executable) and are NOT gated by script-src.
# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

/*
  Strict-Transport-Security: max-age=63072000; includeSubDomains; preload
  X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff
  X-Frame-Options: DENY
  Referrer-Policy: strict-origin-when-cross-origin
  Permissions-Policy: accelerometer=(), ambient-light-sensor=(), autoplay=(), battery=(), camera=(), display-capture=(), document-domain=(), encrypted-media=(), fullscreen=(self), geolocation=(), gyroscope=(), magnetometer=(), microphone=(), midi=(), payment=(), picture-in-picture=(), publickey-credentials-get=(), screen-wake-lock=(), sync-xhr=(), usb=(), web-share=(), xr-spatial-tracking=()
  Cross-Origin-Opener-Policy: same-origin
  Cross-Origin-Resource-Policy: same-site
  Content-Security-Policy: default-src 'self'; script-src 'self' 'unsafe-inline' https://static.cloudflareinsights.com; style-src 'self' 'unsafe-inline' https://fonts.googleapis.com; img-src 'self' data: https://assets.ivaestudios.com; font-src 'self' data: https://fonts.gstatic.com; connect-src 'self' https://cloudflareinsights.com; frame-src 'none'; frame-ancestors 'none'; object-src 'none'; base-uri 'self'; form-action 'self'; upgrade-insecure-requests


# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# 2 · CACHING — per-asset Cache-Control
# ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Strategy:
#   • Byte-stable assets (fonts, hashed-name images) → 1 year + immutable
#   • Mutable but cheap-to-revalidate (CSS, JS, HTML) → 5 minutes +
#     must-revalidate so deploys propagate within minutes.
#   • Crawler-facing text (sitemap, robots, llms) → 1h–1d.
# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════


# Self-hosted brand fonts. WOFF2 binaries are content-addressed by name
# (e.g. inter-variable-latin.woff2) — when we change the subset we
# change the filename, never the content. Pin them for a year +
# immutable so repeat visitors never re-download. Allow CORS so a
# subdomain like assets.ivaestudios.com could request them if needed.
/styles/fonts/*
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=31536000, immutable
  Access-Control-Allow-Origin: *


# Bitmap & vector assets — same logic. Names change before bytes change.
/images/*
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=31536000, immutable


# Direct-served images at root or arbitrary path (fallback for /og.jpg
# and similar). Same long-cache rule.
/*.jpg
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=31536000, immutable

/*.png
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=31536000, immutable

/*.webp
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=31536000, immutable

/*.avif
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=31536000, immutable

/*.svg
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=31536000, immutable


# Main-site CSS. Filenames are NOT hashed (main.css, blog.css, print.css
# stay constant across deploys), so we cannot mark them immutable. 5-min
# TTL + must-revalidate means a CSS change goes live within minutes.
/styles/main.css
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=300, must-revalidate

/styles/blog.css
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=300, must-revalidate

/styles/print.css
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=300, must-revalidate


# Catch-all for the modular CSS pieces (_tokens.css, _nav.css, etc.).
# Same short TTL because the filenames are also stable.
/styles/*.css
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=300, must-revalidate


# Main-site JS — also stable filenames (animations.js, nav.js, etc.).
/js/*.js
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=300, must-revalidate


# Crawler-facing & root-level metadata.
/sitemap.xml
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=3600

/robots.txt
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=86400

/llms.txt
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=86400

/llms-full.txt
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=86400

/site.webmanifest
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=86400
  Content-Type: application/manifest+json


# HTML pages — short TTL so every push to main is live within minutes.
/*.html
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=300, must-revalidate


# Bare-path HTML — the homepage at "/" is matched by this rule.
/
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=300, must-revalidate


# Newsletter / contact endpoints — never cache an API response.
/api/*
  Cache-Control: no-store, no-cache, must-revalidate, max-age=0


# Admin asset that must always be the freshest version.
/focal-admin.js
  Cache-Control: no-store, no-cache, must-revalidate, max-age=0


# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# 3 · GALLERY SUB-APP OVERRIDES (out-of-scope for redesign-2026)
# ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# The gallery sub-app at /gallery/ + /api/gallery/ is owned by the
# gallery team (BRAND.md §11). It needs a permissive CSP because the
# admin UI uses inline event handlers, talks to R2 presigned URLs over
# arbitrary HTTPS hosts, and connects to a localhost uploader daemon
# (127.0.0.1:9876) during admin uploads. These rules are preserved
# verbatim from the previous _headers file.
# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════


# Gallery JS / CSS — short TTL so deploys propagate (no content hashing
# in filenames). Pages MERGES Cache-Control values across matching
# rules, so we must NOT have a wider /*.js or /*.css catch-all that
# would inject `immutable` into these responses.
/gallery/js/*.js
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=300, must-revalidate

/gallery/admin/*.js
  Cache-Control: no-store, no-cache, must-revalidate, max-age=0

/gallery/sw.js
  Cache-Control: no-store, no-cache, must-revalidate, max-age=0
  Service-Worker-Allowed: /

/gallery/css/*.css
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=300, must-revalidate


# Gallery fonts (separate from main-site /styles/fonts/).
/gallery/fonts/*.woff2
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=31536000, immutable
  Access-Control-Allow-Origin: *

/gallery/fonts/fonts.css
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=300, must-revalidate


# Gallery-wide CSP override — permissive on purpose (R2 + localhost).
/gallery/*
  Content-Security-Policy: default-src 'self' https: data: blob:; script-src 'self' 'unsafe-inline' 'unsafe-eval' https:; style-src 'self' 'unsafe-inline' https:; font-src 'self' https: data:; img-src 'self' data: blob: https: http:; media-src 'self' https: blob:; connect-src 'self' https: http://localhost:9876 http://127.0.0.1:9876; worker-src 'self' blob:; frame-src 'self' https:; frame-ancestors 'self'; base-uri 'self'; form-action 'self'
  X-Frame-Options: SAMEORIGIN
  X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff
  Referrer-Policy: strict-origin-when-cross-origin
  Strict-Transport-Security: max-age=31536000; includeSubDomains; preload


# Gallery API — never cache.
/api/gallery/*
  Cache-Control: no-store, no-cache, must-revalidate, max-age=0
  X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff
  Referrer-Policy: strict-origin-when-cross-origin


# Admin pages — never cache (deploys propagate immediately).
/gallery/admin/*
  Cache-Control: no-store, no-cache, must-revalidate, max-age=0
  Pragma: no-cache

/gallery/admin/
  Cache-Control: no-store, no-cache, must-revalidate, max-age=0


# Gallery client view — fresh HTML, immutable assets stay cached.
/gallery/gallery.html
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=0, must-revalidate


# Login + auth pages — fresh HTML.
/gallery/index.html
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=0, must-revalidate

/gallery/galleries.html
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=0, must-revalidate
